# Crash Course to KUL Course -- Advanced Analytics in a Big Data World

After burning ~200 dollars worth of Opus-4-8 tokens in Claude Code, I present to you a crash course for KUL's Big Data course preparation, vintage 2026.

This is also a small experiment in questioning Belgium's exam-oriented higher education: is it still worth sitting through every lecture and reviewing every slide, or can you learn more -- and score better -- by first unlearning KUL?

## Structure

```
.claude         
Notes/          # Original lecture slides (PDFs)
summary/        # Per-chapter HTML summaries + cheat sheet + combined overview
prepare/        # Per-chapter exam-prep guides (deeper, with intuition checks)
Exam/           # Past exams & solutions + 4 AI-generated mock exams
```

## Using Claude Code to study

This repo ships with a `.claude/SKILLS.md` that turns Claude Code into an adaptive tutor. Open the project in Claude Code, pick a chapter, and ask it to teach you -- it will quiz you, drill into your weak spots, and won't let you move on until you've actually understood the material. Think of it as a Socratic study partner that never gets tired.

Either way, I hope this helps someone out there. Good luck with your exam! No matter which year you are.
